PN,41404
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F414A1777903638
OL,3,CHMS Victory masts successfully removed
OL,4,Cin #42 million restoration project
OL,6,FA scaffolding structure will now
OL,7,Fenclose the ship and remain in place
OL,8,Funtil the conservation work is
OL,9,Fcompleted in 2033.
OL,11,FHMS Victory, which is the world's
OL,12,Foldest commissioned warship, was
OL,13,FNelson's flagship at the Battle of
OL,14,FTrafalgar and it was on the ship's
OL,15,Fquarterdeck that he was fatally shot
OL,16,Fby a French sniper on October 21 1805.
OL,18,FVictory was first floated out at
OL,19,FChatham in 1765 but by the 1920s was
OL,20,Fin poor condition and moved to dry
OL,21,Fdock in Portsmouth, Hampshire, in 1922.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
